article.headline: Louisiana Tech 71, San Jose St. 67
article.story: SAN JOSE, Calif. -- Brandon Gibson and Raheem Appleby each scored 19 points and Louisiana Tech beat San Jose State 71-67 on Saturday night. Trevor Gaskins scored 12 points, including a pair of free throws in the final two seconds that sealed it for the Bulldogs (10-10, 2/3 Western Athletic). The Bulldogs won their second straight after a four-game losing streak. James Kinney scored 22 points to lead the Spartans (6-13, 0-5), who lost their fifth straight. Wil Carter had 12 points and 11 rebounds while Keith Shamburger added 16 points. San Jose State had a 33-31 lead at halftime.
